  "body": "**üßê Motivation**\r\nHi, \r\nI recently used openzepplin-contracts/ERC20Capped for my start-up Metarei.net, I found the code and documentation to be excellent thank you.\r\n\r\nAdditionally I wanted to have a simple unlock mechanism that would gradually release the token supply to make it more difficult for speculators to control price and allow us to get a better average sale price as we mature and develop the products.\r\n\r\nIf this feature interests you please let me know and I will raise a PR. \r\n\r\n**üìù Details**\r\nThe contract take an additional 'unlocks' parameter which is an array of unix timestamps. The mint function uses a similar algo as BTC in that there is a halving of the released supply at each unlock. \r\n\r\nOnce the unlocks have passed the owner can call mint at any time and will issued whatever tokens are available from burning for example. \r\n\r\nPlease see [ERC20HalvingReleaseSchedule](https://github.com/Metarei-network/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/ERC20HalvingReleaseSchedule/contracts/token/ERC20/extensions/ERC20HalvingReleaseSchedule.sol)\r\n\r\n\r\nThank you\r\n\r\nTom",
