    "body": "Hello @Metarei-network \r\n\r\nAs far as token release goes, we already include vesting contracts. My go to solution would thus be to mint whatever you want (during the constructor ?) and have these tokens owner by a vesting wallet that will control the release. To implement your particular schedule you might need to override the [`_vestingSchedule`](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/blob/master/contracts/finance/VestingWallet.sol#L126-L134) function. But it should be relatively easy.\r\n\r\nYou proposal might work for your particular case, but IMO it loses a lot of the generality that we want to have with our contracts. In particular, you are tightly coupling ERC20 with Ownable ... also you are considering a very specific halvening flow with unlock timestamp ... which might be good for you, but is not generic at all.\r\n\r\nIn the end, I would argue that your implementation is very specific to a particular release schedule, but would have to be significantly re-writtend is anyone wanted to modify it. Our approach is to provide \"mostly ready to use\" contract. and anything that needs to be significantly re-written to be specialized isn't where we want to go.",
